text.0: I just had a very constructive dialogue with :Germany: Chancellor Merkel about the #COVID19 situation. I am impressed, as always, with her leadership and commitment. We agreed that countries must work together to suppress the virus, and that each and every one of us has a role to play. https://t.co/z3n5H5mYtn
text.1:
"We cannot give up... We must not give up... 
The fight back against this #COVID19 pandemic is everyone’s business."

Full text of @DrTedros' opening remarks at the media briefing on #COVID19 - 26 October 2020 https://t.co/gP9BtVyggM
text.2:
"I hope the knowledge gained through this course will act as a catalyst for health policies that include migrants and refugee communities. 
#HealthForAll, means all."-@DrTedros 

https://t.co/y6OrElijw4
text.3:
"All of public health suffers when any community is excluded. 
It's vital that all countries include refugees and migrants in their national policies as part of their commitment to #HealthForAll."-@DrTedros
text.4:
"There were people attending from 122 different countries worldwide and I would like to take this opportunity to congratulate all involved in this course."-@DrTedros 

https://t.co/y6OrElijw4
text.5:
"The course included being directly connected live with health and migration projects on the ground so that they could receive direct feedback from those in the field."-@DrTedros 
https://t.co/y6OrElijw4
text.6: "Finally, last week WHO conducted its first global e-learning course on health and migration, addressing a critical and often neglected topic of global health."-@DrTedros
text.7:
"A pandemic is not a political football. Wishful thinking or deliberate diversion will not prevent transmissions or save lives. 
What will save lives is science, solutions and solidarity."-@DrTedros on #COVID19 

https://t.co/Ms3iSeUfrN
text.8:
"This is why I have said repeatedly: stop the politicisation of #COVID19."-@DrTedros 

https://t.co/BcuKiz6MX1
text.9: "But where there has been political division at the national level; where there has been blatant disrespect for science and health professionals, confusion has spread and #COVID19 cases and deaths have mounted."-@DrTedros
text.10: "For leaders, as my colleague @DrMikeRyan said back in March, the most important thing to do is to “move fast, have no regrets.”"-@DrTedros on #COVID19
text.11:
"From Dakar to Melbourne, Milan to Islamabad, New York to Beijing. 
When leaders act quickly and deliberately, the virus can be suppressed."-@DrTedros on #COVID19
text.12:
"Many countries and cities have followed the science, suppressed the virus and minimized deaths."-@DrTedros on #COVID19

https://t.co/Mt66kcwMbC
text.13:
"Science continues to tell us the truth about this virus. 
How to contain it, suppress it and stop it from returning, and how to save lives among those it reaches."-@DrTedros on #COVID19
text.14: "And then, once you have the upper hand, it’s important to strengthen health systems, the health workforce and contact tracing systems so that the virus doesn’t take hold again."-@DrTedros on #COVID19
text.15: "There aren’t magic solutions to this #COVID19 outbreak, just hard work from leaders at all levels of societies, health workers, contact tracers and individuals."-@DrTedros
text.16:
"With these measures, you can catch-up to this virus, you can get ahead of this virus, and you can stay ahead of this virus. We say this because we have seen in many places around the world get ahead and stay ahead of the virus"-@DrTedros on #COVID19

https://t.co/H08ZtW43jZ
text.17:
"For governments, it means doing the same things we have been calling for since day one: know your #COVID19 epidemic. 
:white_heavy_check_mark: Break the chains of transmission.
:white_heavy_check_mark: Test extensively.
:white_heavy_check_mark: Isolate and care for cases.
:white_heavy_check_mark: Trace & provide supported quarantine for all contacts."-@DrTedros
text.18:
"Furthermore, you continue to
:white_heavy_check_mark: maintain physical distance
:white_heavy_check_mark: #WearAMask
:white_heavy_check_mark: cleaning your hands regularly
:white_heavy_check_mark: coughing away from others
:white_heavy_check_mark: avoiding crowds or meeting friends and family outside."
-@DrTedros
https://t.co/w2m7rA2HoT
text.19: "For individuals, families & communities, that means staying at home & especially if you’ve been exposed to a #COVID19 case"-@DrTedros
text.20:
"We can keep our kids in school, we can keep businesses open, we can preserve lives and livelihoods. We can do it. 
But we must all make trade-offs, compromises and sacrifices."-@DrTedros on #COVID19
text.21:
"We cannot have the economic recovery we want and live our lives the way we did before the #COVID19 pandemic."
-@DrTedros
text.22:
"No one wants more so-called #COVID19 lockdowns. But if we want to avoid them, we all have to play our part."
-@DrTedros
text.23: "We must do all we can to protect #HealthWorkers, and the best way to do that is for all of us to take every precaution we can to reduce the risk of #COVID19 transmission, for ourselves and others."-@DrTedros
text.24:
"In March, health workers were routinely applauded for the personal sacrifice they were making to save lives. 
Many of those #HealthWorkers, who have themselves gone through immense stress & trauma, are still on the frontlines, facing a fresh wave of new patients"-@DrTedros
text.25: "Leaders must balance the #COVID19 disruption to lives and livelihoods with the need to protect health workers and health systems as intensive care fills up."-@DrTedros
text.26:
"Working from home, children being schooled remotely, not being able to celebrate milestones with friends and family or not being there to mourn loved ones – it’s tough and the #COVID19 fatigue is real. 
But we cannot give up. We must not give up."-@DrTedros
text.27:
"We understand the #COVID19 pandemic fatigue that people are feeling. 
It takes a mental and physical toll on everyone."-@DrTedros
text.28: "Over the weekend, a number of leaders critically evaluated their #COVID19 situation and took action to limit the spread of the virus."-@DrTedros
text.29:
"Last week saw the highest number of #COVID19 cases reported so far. 
Many countries in the northern hemisphere are seeing a concerning rise in cases & hospitalisations.
And ICUs are filling up to capacity in some places, particularly in Europe & North America."-@DrTedros
text.31: Please note that today's virtual press conference, previously scheduled at 5.00PM CEST, has been postponed and will now start at 5.30PM.
text.32: “The trajectory of this pandemic is in our hands, as it has been since the beginning,” says @mvankerkhove in an interview with the @Telegraph on the #COVID19 pandemic. https://t.co/GdjcdNQtyW
text.33: 9 tonnes of medical kits, medicines for 2000 people and personal protective equipment for 4000 #healthworkers have reached #Syria at a critical time, when the number of #COVID19 cases is expected to rise. For more info, reach out to our media team. https://t.co/JCrqwh6sjV
text.34: Pleased to address the @Bundestag this morning. I thanked :Germany: for its visionary leadership in global health. @WHO is committed to strengthening our engagement with the Bundestag & with all parliaments, which play a critical role in moving the :globe_showing_Europe-Africa: health agenda forward #HealthForAll https://t.co/zUCOkq0f5T
text.35:
Accountability is at the core of our work across the world.
